<div>
    <h2>"The future depends on what you do today."</h2>
    <h4>Mahatma Gandi</h4>
    <p>Below you will find several resources that can help with getting you started on writing this new chapter of you life. We're all with you!&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
</div>
<section>
    <h3>Finding a Job</h3>
        <ul>
            <li> <a href="https://www.prisonfellowship.org/resources/support-friends-family-of-prisoners/supporting-successful-prisoner-reentry/how-to-find-a-job-after-prison/">How To Find A Job After Prison from Prison Fellowship</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://www.prisonfellowship.org/resources/support-friends-family-of-prisoners/supporting-successful-prisoner-reentry/how-to-find-a-job-after-prison/">Employment Information Handbook for Ex-offenders from the US Department of Labor</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://www.monster.com/career-advice/article/resume-dilemma-criminal-record">Resume Dilema: Criminal Record from Monster</a> </li> 
        </ul>
        <p id=applyingAdvice>Apply everywhere possible and don't forget to follow-up!</p>
        <ul>
            <li> <a href="https://www.monster.com/">Monster</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://www.indeed.com/">Indeed</a> </li> 
            <li> <a href="https://www.ziprecruiter.com/">ZipRecruiter</a> </li>
        </ul>
</section>
<section>
    <h3>Finding a Home</h3>
        <ul>
            <li> <a href="https://www.careeronestop.org/ExOffender/default.aspx">CareerOneStop for Ex-Offenders</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://www.recordgone.com/articles/reentry-programs-for-minnesota-ex-offenders.htm">Reentry Programs For Ex-Offenders In Minnesota</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://mn.gov/doc/assets/Housing_Resources-MN_American_Indian_Transition_Resource_Directory_tcm1089-276284.pdf">Housing Resources from the Minnesota State Government</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://www.prisonfellowship.org/resources/training-resources/reentry-ministry/on-going-ministry/helping-ex-prisoners-find-housing/">Helping Ex-prisoners Find Housing from Prison Fellowship</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://www.ojp.gov/pdffiles1/203374.pdf">Guide For Developing Housing For Ex-Offenders from the US Department of Justice</a></li>
        </ul>
</section>
<section>
    <h3>Continuing Education</h3>
        <ul>
            <li> <a href="https://freegrantsforfelons.org/grants-and-scholarships-for-felons-going-back-to-college/">Grants and Scholarships for Felons Going Back to College</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://lendedu.com/blog/scholarships-for-felons/">Financial Aid and Scholarships for Felons from LendEDU</a> </li>
            <li> <a href="https://www.affordablecollegesonline.org/college-resource-center/college-after-prison/">Colleges and Degrees for Felons from Affordable Colleges</a> </li>
        </ul>
</section>
<div>
    <h3>Substance Abuse and Mental Health Support</h3>
    <ul>
        <li> <a href="https://www.prisonfellowship.org/resources/training-resources/reentry-ministry/on-going-ministry/encouraging-a-life-of-sobriety/">Encouraging a Life of Sobriety from Prison Fellowship</a> </li>
        <li> <a href="https://www.samhsa.gov/find-help/national-helpline"> Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration Hotline</a> </li>
        <li> <a href="https://www.nami.org/Your-Journey/Individuals-with-Mental-Illness/Reentry-After-a-Period-of-Incarceration">Reentry After a Period of Incarceration from the National Alliance on Mental Illness</a> </li>
        <li> <a href="https://www.wellnessrecoveryactionplan.com/wrap-is-helping-ex-offenders-find-new-lives-in-the-community/">Helping Ex-Offenders Find New Lives in the Community through Wellness Recovery Action Plan or WRAP</a> </li>
    </ul>
